events.name: GDG Peshawar Launch & Next '19 Extended
events.description:
As you all are aware of our new chapter, GDG Peshawar starting recently, we're excited to invite you all to this launch event including a Cloud Next '19 Extended as well.

It will be a fun-filled event full of tech-geeks, tech-lovers and community builders focused on what GDG Peshawar plans to do for the ecosystem of Peshawar and the whole Khyber Pakhtunkhwa. We will have speakers working in the government, community builders and individuals expert in Google tools such as TensorFlow, Cloud, Firebase, Flutter and Kotlin.

This event is for those who are:
- Geeks
- Technology Lovers
- Web/Software/Mobile Developers
- Software Engineering/Computer Science Students

A surprise session is also planned specifically for the female attendees and that will be announced later. Stay tuned, excited and see you there.

Register here: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdT4uYaI7CtvkCwFUvWtuKjMp-tt1mkI8SgrfTcWaQj4qCvbA/viewform
events.how_to_find_us:
Google Maps Link: https://goo.gl/maps/gDvRg1TVMWk

The location is inside the PTCL Training center.

events.name: DSC Application Drive
events.description:
Google collaborates with university students who are passionate about growing developer communities and supports them with starting student clubs on their campuses. Developer Student Clubs help thousands of student developers learn and work with their communities to solve real-life problems.

This is for those students who still has 2 years left until their graduation.

We invite you to join us at this Application Drive event for an awareness session so we can guide you through the benefits of joining the DSCs and how to apply for it.

Register here for the event: https://forms.gle/UGo2Yr3hKaQebikj9

events.name: I/O Extended 2019 Peshawar
events.description:
Google I/O (Simply I/O) is an annual developers conference hosted by Google to bring together developers from around the globe annually for talks, hands-on learning with Google experts, and the first look at Googleâ€™s latest developer products. I/O showcases technical in-depth sessions focused on building web, mobile, and enterprise applications with Google and open sources such as Android, Chrome and Chrome OS, APIs, Google Web Toolkit, App Engine, and more.

I/O Extended events are held around the world for developers to take part in the I/O experience. This year I/O extended event is going to be the biggest one featuring many amazing speakers including experts from Google. This is the opportunity to learn major Google technologies through exclusive sessions and code labs.

The technology/topics we will be featuring for I/O Extended 2019 Peshawar are:

'Kotlin' and 'Flutter'.

Requirements: Bring Charged Laptops

Free refreshments will be served after the event!

upcoming.name: The Art of Public Speaking by WTM Peshawar
upcoming.description:
*This event is being organized GDG Peshawar & Women Techmakers Peshawar.*

We're organising this event at Abbottabad and the theme of the event is, "Speak to Lead". Public Speaking is no longer a Soft Skill. It is the key to success and thus we are organising this workshop to help you develop your speaking skills.

About Women Techmakers Peshawar:

Women Techmakers Peshawar is an independent group; our activities and the opinions expressed on this Page should in no way be linked to Google, the corporation.
